BENOC ANNEXURE CONVERTER
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

New file: benoc_annexure_convertor.py

Adopts safe_json_parse, multi-page rasterization, bulk-isolation pattern from 
the LATEST working RS converter. Do not copy the EI or DEG/EG converters — 
copy from RS which incorporates all the fixes.

Per-annexure extraction schema (annexure_type determines which fields are 
populated):

MAIN_APPLICATION_DOCUMENT:
  Extracts everything the approved main doc contains:
  - product_name, dosage_form, batch_number, mfg_date
  - apis[]: name, iupac_name, molecular_formula, molecular_weight, cas_number, 
    therapeutic_category, indications[], manufacturer, manufacturer_address
  - manufacturing_address: test_batch_address, be_batch_address
  - regulatory_status
  - raw_materials[]: sno, name, specification, function
  - composition[]: {stage_name, rows: [{ingredient, role, mg_per_tab}], 
    subtotal_label, subtotal_value}
  - equipment[]: sno, name, make_model
  - manufacturing_process[]: {subtitle, narrative}
  - process_flow: {steps[], footnote, image_b64 if present}
  - drug_substance_specs (per API): [{sno, test, sub_tests[], specification}]
  - patent_status
  - innovator: {generic_name, brand_name, strength, manufacturer}
  - finished_product_spec[]: {sno, test, specification}
  - dissolution: {media_description, reference_batch, test_batch, tables[]}

STABILITY_FILE:
  - storage_condition (e.g., "40°C/75%RH")
  - batch_number, stability_batch_number, batch_size
  - mfg_date, study_initiation_date, protocol_no
  - pack, testing_frequency, ar_numbers
  - timepoints[] (e.g., ["Initial", "1M", "6M"])
  - results[]: {characteristic, specification, values: [initial, 1M, 6M, ...]}

MANUFACTURING_LICENSE (Form 25, Form 28, GMP cert):
  - license_number
  - license_form (25 / 28 / GMP)
  - manufacturing_address
  - issue_date, validity_date
  - certifying_authority
  - certificate_id

TEST_LICENSE (Form 29):
  - license_number
  - manufacturing_address
  - approved_products[]: {generic_name, composition, pack_size}
  - issue_date, validity_years
  - regulatory_authority

MANUFACTURING_LOCATION_DECLARATION:
  - test_batch_address
  - be_batch_address
  - prepared_by, checked_by, envelope_id

RLD_UTILIZATION:
  - product_name (test), brand_name (RLD), manufacturer (RLD)
  - class_of_drug, country, pack_and_count, total_quantity
  - breakup[]: {sno, description, quantity}
  - declared_by, title, company_address

NARCOTIC_DECLARATION:
  - product_name
  - ndps_reference (e.g., "NDPS Act 1985")
  - declaration_text (verbatim)
  - declared_by, title, company_address

STP_DOCUMENT:
  - stp_number, stp_version
  - applicable_product
  - tests_covered[]: brief list of test names only
  - NO deep extraction (no methods, mobile phases, wavelengths)

Converter must auto-classify annexure_type from content patterns:
  - "PRODUCT NAME:" + multi-section document with drug info + composition
    → main_application_document
  - "STABILITY DATA" + "Storage condition" + batch info → stability_file
  - "Form 25" / "Form 28" / "GOOD MANUFACTURING PRACTICES" → manufacturing_license
  - "Form 29" / "test license" → test_license
  - "MANUFACTURING ADDRESS" as short declaration → manufacturing_location_declaration
  - "UTILIZATION BREAKUP" / "quantity to be imported" → rld_utilization
  - "NDPS Act 1985" / "Narcotic and Psychotropic" → narcotic_declaration
  - "STP" / "Standard Test Procedure" / long multi-page procedure document 
    → stp_document

Fallback: annexure_type = "generic" with material_name and raw_text preserved.

